Nigeria on Sunday defeated Egypt in Casablanca at the ongoing All African Games 3-0 to qualify for the final of the Badminton team event. The victory has now set the stage for the final against Algeria later on Sunday. The game opened with the mixed doubles as Doha Hanny and Adham El Gamal paired against the Nigerian duo of Enejoh Abah and Peace Orji. READ ALSO: 12th African Games: Igali charges wrestlers to give ‘best efforts’ in Morocco The Nigerians won 21-15, 21-15 and 21-19. In the men’s singles, Anuoluwapo Opeyori beat Mostafa Kamel 21-14 and 21-12, while Dorcas Adesokan completed the rout with a 21-10, 21-11 defeat of Hadia Hosny in the female category. (NAN) VANGUARD Team Nigeria has bagged three gold medals in the ongoing 2nd edition of the African Youth Games holding in Gaborone, Botswana. May 25, 2014 In "Sports" Team Nigeria on Friday suffered defeat against Egypt in the female semi-finals of the ongoing African Nations Beach Volleyball Senior Men and Women Championships in Abuja. April 27, 2019 In "News" Nigeria on Sunday won the third place in the ongoing African Women Beach Volleyball 2016 Olympics Qualifiers at the Jabi lakeside in Abuja. April 18, 2016 In "Sports"